A pastor and three others allegedly kidnapped by herders at Ogwashi-Uku in Aniocha South Local Government of Delta State have regained freedom. The Nation learnt that the victims spent four days in captivity. Police spokesman DSP Onome Onowakpoyeya confirmed the release of the victims. He said: “They have been  released. This is all I can tell you. Whether ransom was paid or not, I don’t know.” It was gathered that the victims were abducted at Comprehensive Secondary School on Ubulu-Unor road in  Ogwashi-Uku. The kidnappers, suspected to be herders, demanded N100million ransom.